WEBVTT

00:34.660 --> 00:37.287
[footsteps trudging]

00:43.377 --> 00:45.587
[footsteps continue]

00:52.719 --> 00:54.805
[wind blowing, leaves rustling]

01:23.792 --> 01:26.003
My mother was not a fortunate woman.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.089
And bringing me into the world

01:29.173 --> 01:31.175
was a great burden for her to bear.

01:33.385 --> 01:36.555
When I was still very young, she passed.

01:38.140 --> 01:40.309
Grieving, my father took to drink.

01:40.893 --> 01:43.228
Which is why myselfand my three older sisters

01:43.312 --> 01:45.397
wound up begging in the village.

01:46.565 --> 01:49.985
The matchmakercame to my father one day…

01:51.486 --> 01:55.991
and told him of a familywith a boarding house in Dongsam.

01:56.074 --> 01:59.912
Their son had a cleft lipand was unmarried, of course.

02:01.121 --> 02:03.624
I was offered up gladly.

02:05.626 --> 02:08.794
That was aboutthree years ago, a little more.

02:08.878 --> 02:12.633
I've tried my very best to do rightby their family and my husband.

02:17.429 --> 02:19.223
I've given birth to three sons.

02:22.309 --> 02:24.603
None lived to see his first birthday.

02:27.564 --> 02:29.566
If it were only me,

02:29.650 --> 02:31.652
I could weather the shock.

02:32.444 --> 02:33.862
But my husband…

02:35.155 --> 02:37.241
He is the kindest of men.[breathes shakily]

02:40.869 --> 02:43.997
I am with child, but…

02:46.041 --> 02:48.669
I think there is some curse on my blood.

02:56.301 --> 02:58.929
[siren wailing in distance]

03:25.664 --> 03:26.665
[elevator dings]

03:28.959 --> 03:30.836
[phones ringing]

03:40.262 --> 03:43.140
[manager 1, in English]Listen, there's no easy way to say this.

03:43.974 --> 03:46.143
You're not getting the bump.

03:46.226 --> 03:47.352
Not this year.

03:47.436 --> 03:49.730
I know we gave youall the signs otherwise,

03:49.813 --> 03:52.232
-but the 43rd floor believes…-[pager beeping]

03:52.316 --> 03:55.777
… it's better for you if you haveone more year under your belt.

04:02.409 --> 04:03.410
I want to know why.

04:03.493 --> 04:05.746
He told you why.They don't think you're ready.

04:06.371 --> 04:08.498
Keep busting ahead,doing what you're doing, and--

04:08.582 --> 04:10.209
I helped close the Teestone merger.

04:10.292 --> 04:11.710
Handled Brixley's buyout.

04:11.793 --> 04:13.629
Number one on my leaderboard for two--

04:13.712 --> 04:15.964
It's not your year, okay?

04:21.637 --> 04:24.681
[spouse] Please call onmy ancestors to lift this curse

04:24.765 --> 04:26.600
so we can have a family.

04:31.855 --> 04:34.066
[sighs] Mmm.

04:51.208 --> 04:53.836
[drum beating slowly]

04:57.840 --> 04:59.174
[exhales heavily]

05:01.510 --> 05:03.428
Colt-- C-Colton Hotels.

05:04.054 --> 05:06.098
Priority client, itching to go public.

05:06.181 --> 05:08.183
Their valuation needs an adrenaline shot.

05:08.809 --> 05:09.893
They need that hotel.

05:09.977 --> 05:11.186
That's in Tokyo.

05:11.270 --> 05:14.439
Where one landowner, one,holds the entire deal hostage.

05:14.523 --> 05:16.358
[drum beating faster]

05:21.905 --> 05:23.824
[employee] She's Korean, the landowner.

05:26.118 --> 05:28.704
Doesn't mean anything to you, I know.But I'm telling you…

05:29.288 --> 05:30.581
I can close that deal.

05:33.959 --> 05:35.085
[manager 2] What do you know?

05:35.169 --> 05:39.131
A 300-plus room hotelat a 150 to 200 million build cost.

05:40.883 --> 05:41.800
[breathes shakily]

05:41.884 --> 05:46.221
Back of the napkin calculations say10-15 million payday for us.

05:46.305 --> 05:49.641
And this landowner, her being Korean,you think that'll give you an in?

05:49.725 --> 05:52.060
Wait, I'm confused here.I thought you were Japanese.

05:52.144 --> 05:54.188
No, I just grew up there.

05:55.564 --> 05:58.192
-[manager 2] You sure about this?-Yes, I'm sure.

05:59.067 --> 06:02.613
And once I close this deal,I want to be transferred back right away. And once I close this deal,I want to be transferred back right away.

06:04.740 --> 06:08.660
I want that VP titleand the raise backdated to today's date.

06:10.621 --> 06:13.248
And I want my year-end bonus to reflect

06:13.332 --> 06:16.543
just how muchColton Hotels means to this firm.

06:19.004 --> 06:20.506
[drum stops]

06:20.589 --> 06:22.216
And I would like all this in writing.

06:23.842 --> 06:25.052
[spouse breathes shakily]

06:26.803 --> 06:29.223
True, a child is coming.

06:30.641 --> 06:33.977
She will thrive, I assure you.

06:35.437 --> 06:38.690
And through her, a family will endure.

06:42.861 --> 06:46.490
[screams]

06:52.120 --> 06:53.121
[sighs]

06:55.624 --> 06:57.835
[midwife] Come now! Hurry!

06:59.294 --> 07:02.339
[crying] [crying]

07:03.465 --> 07:04.800
[midwife] Listen to her cry.

07:04.883 --> 07:06.510
She's a handful all right.

07:07.261 --> 07:08.720
Thank you so much.

07:08.804 --> 07:10.764
[midwife] Take good care of her.

07:10.848 --> 07:11.974
[chuckles]

07:13.392 --> 07:15.561
[father] This one will put up a fight.

07:17.563 --> 07:19.022
We must name her now.

07:41.753 --> 07:42.754
[father] Sunja!

07:43.422 --> 07:44.423
[exclaims]

07:51.138 --> 07:52.347
[father] Sunja!

07:53.932 --> 07:55.142
[sighs]

08:00.522 --> 08:01.523
Mmm.

08:14.912 --> 08:16.121
[chuckles]

08:19.750 --> 08:20.751
Oh.

