27:53.257 --> 27:54.424
[sighs]

27:54.508 --> 27:55.509
[grunts] Oh.

27:56.385 --> 27:57.594
What is it?

27:58.220 --> 27:59.638
Why didn't you stop him?

28:01.890 --> 28:03.350
How could I have?

28:03.433 --> 28:04.726
If anyone says something…

28:04.810 --> 28:05.769
No, they won't.

28:05.853 --> 28:08.605
They've slept under our rooffor a long time now.

28:08.689 --> 28:10.774
-It only takes one to---Hey, shh.

28:13.986 --> 28:15.404
Calm down already.

28:16.738 --> 28:19.157
We do no wrong. Why would they arrest us?

28:20.033 --> 28:23.036
After all he just said,we go on feeding and housing him?

28:23.120 --> 28:24.121
Isn't that wrong?

28:24.830 --> 28:26.915
If the Japanese come for us,

28:26.999 --> 28:28.792
who will take care of Sunja?

28:29.751 --> 28:32.045
It'll work out in the end, you'll see.

28:32.129 --> 28:34.006
-We can't let it…-You don't know that--

28:34.089 --> 28:35.299
There, there…

28:38.510 --> 28:40.929
Well, sir, is your belly full?

28:42.055 --> 28:45.559
Ma'am, you do feed us so well.

28:45.642 --> 28:47.644
You are too kind to us, really.

28:47.728 --> 28:48.937
Our pleasure.

29:17.174 --> 29:18.175
[chuckles]

29:22.888 --> 29:24.890
Sunja, what?

29:25.390 --> 29:27.267
Last night you said stupid things.

29:27.351 --> 29:29.353
And now they're all scared.

29:30.354 --> 29:33.607
They're all… Who exactly is all?

29:33.690 --> 29:37.277
Everybody is scared.But no one says anything.

29:38.403 --> 29:40.405
Now they all want you to leave.

29:42.658 --> 29:45.494
But where would I go?I have nowhere to go.

29:45.577 --> 29:48.622
It doesn't matter where.Any place. Just go.

29:52.584 --> 29:54.169
Sunja.

29:54.253 --> 29:56.338
I had too much to drink.

29:56.421 --> 29:59.925
And those are the kind of words you saywhen you have no power.

30:00.008 --> 30:01.635
But you understand that.

30:02.594 --> 30:03.428
I don't want…

30:04.221 --> 30:07.850
… to use a rock on a Japanese manand crush his skull.

30:08.725 --> 30:10.686
And I don't want my parents to be gone.

30:11.812 --> 30:13.188
I don't want to be alone.

30:14.189 --> 30:15.607
I would rather die.

30:21.280 --> 30:23.115
Sunja, listen.

30:23.699 --> 30:24.992
Forget all that.

30:25.909 --> 30:28.328
Forget about all I said.

30:29.037 --> 30:30.289
I, y'know…

30:30.372 --> 30:33.208
I'm a man who no longer knowshow to live in this world.

30:35.544 --> 30:36.545
Understand?

30:39.840 --> 30:40.716
Good.

30:43.010 --> 30:44.011
[sighs]

31:19.505 --> 31:22.341
[officer 1] When was the last timeyou saw Song, the fisherman?

31:23.342 --> 31:25.219
[mother] It's been a few days.

31:25.302 --> 31:27.429
[officer 1]Where do you think he might have gone?

31:30.641 --> 31:33.435
[Sunja's mother]I am sorry. I don't know his business.

31:33.519 --> 31:36.063
[conversation continues, indistinct]

31:43.111 --> 31:44.112
Papa!

31:45.113 --> 31:46.198
Papa!

31:48.700 --> 31:49.701
Papa!

31:52.162 --> 31:53.580
Papa!

31:56.416 --> 31:57.626
Papa!

31:59.628 --> 32:00.629
Papa! Papa!

32:13.350 --> 32:16.979
[father] We never noticed any signsof disloyalty in him before.

32:18.313 --> 32:20.274
But he left all his things behind.

32:21.692 --> 32:23.944
And he still owes us two months' rent.

32:31.285 --> 32:34.329
That night… What exactly happened?

32:35.831 --> 32:38.375
He had much too much to drink, you see.

32:38.458 --> 32:40.836
And for you, that's an excuse?

32:45.883 --> 32:46.884
No…

32:48.302 --> 32:49.428
No, no.

32:49.511 --> 32:54.183
I assure you, officer, we were allvery shocked by the things he said.

32:55.851 --> 32:57.603
And yet you didn't report it at the time.

33:01.481 --> 33:05.027
If you see or hearsuch traitorous activities,

33:05.110 --> 33:07.112
it's your duty to report them.

33:09.281 --> 33:12.701
-Sir, I---[shouts] How dare you interrupt me!

33:19.166 --> 33:24.379
We give our progress, our innovations,our education to these idiots…

33:25.797 --> 33:28.634
… only to be lied to our faces.

33:28.717 --> 33:29.635
[officer 1] Calm down.

33:30.219 --> 33:33.597
Let's just end this with a warning.

33:33.680 --> 33:36.600
[officer 2]Maybe we've gotten too soft on them.

33:36.683 --> 33:37.851
[officer 1] We had no choice.

33:37.935 --> 33:39.937
Push them too hard and they'll explode.

33:44.525 --> 33:46.401
There will be no second chances.

33:48.946 --> 33:51.657
If you have news of this man,you'll let us know.

33:52.824 --> 33:53.825
Hmm?

34:00.123 --> 34:02.960
Madam, I hear your cookingis praiseworthy.

34:04.127 --> 34:07.965
I'll have to come backjust to see if it's as good as they say.

34:09.591 --> 34:12.803
Oh… Of course, anytime you like.

34:14.096 --> 34:15.097
Let's go.

34:41.956 --> 34:43.958
Did somebody tell him to run away?

34:44.918 --> 34:46.335
How else would he know?

34:47.545 --> 34:48.964
I didn't tell him anything.

34:57.222 --> 35:00.434
[door opens, closes] [door opens, closes]

35:04.688 --> 35:08.400
There's no way we can eat all of this.You're making too much.

35:08.483 --> 35:10.360
You must eat.

35:10.444 --> 35:11.570
Look in the mirror!

35:12.613 --> 35:15.073
You're too thin. All skin and bones.

35:15.157 --> 35:16.783
Put the green onions in.

35:18.410 --> 35:20.537
-[gasps]-Oh dear.

35:20.621 --> 35:22.873
Put some cold water on it. [sighs]

35:23.665 --> 35:25.334
Clearly you don't cook for yourself.

35:25.417 --> 35:27.920
Just like your father,a slave to your job.

35:30.214 --> 35:34.009
I told him to sell the pachinko parlor.Real estate is booming right now.

35:34.092 --> 35:36.011
He should invest in stores or housing.

35:36.094 --> 35:38.597
-So he hasn't told you?-Told me what?

35:38.680 --> 35:40.849
He's opening a second parlor this year.

35:42.935 --> 35:44.061
Don't look so shocked.

35:44.144 --> 35:46.396
He's been thinking about it.You knew that.

35:48.315 --> 35:49.733
And how will he finance it?

35:49.816 --> 35:51.652
How do you think?

35:51.735 --> 35:53.820
Go down to the bank and just get a loan.

35:55.781 --> 35:58.450
He's proud of what he's built.

35:59.284 --> 36:02.246
And he doesn't need your shameto knock him down the ladder. And he doesn't need your shameto knock him down the ladder.

36:02.955 --> 36:04.748
What does shame have to do with this?

36:04.831 --> 36:06.625
You don't need to say it,I know it's there.

36:06.708 --> 36:10.629
I know what it looks like,I have a lot of experience with it.

36:10.712 --> 36:12.381
I know how to smell it and I can hear it.

36:15.342 --> 36:16.969
Now go and fetch me an egg.

36:26.728 --> 36:28.021
All right, tell me. Be honest.

36:28.981 --> 36:32.192
You're going back, right?You're not going to stay here?

36:33.151 --> 36:34.236
What do you mean by that?

36:35.112 --> 36:39.533
Some, like your dad, can fool themselvesabout how things have changed.

36:39.616 --> 36:41.827
I know that's not the case.

36:43.203 --> 36:44.830
You're safer in America.

36:45.914 --> 36:47.457
What am I safe from exactly?

36:48.292 --> 36:49.585
[front door closes]

36:49.668 --> 36:50.711
[visitor] Solomon?

36:50.794 --> 36:52.588
-Solomon!-Etsuko!

36:52.671 --> 36:53.755
-[sighs]-[chuckles]

36:53.839 --> 36:57.467
I'm sorry but the restaurant was so busy.I couldn't leave earlier.

36:58.135 --> 37:00.012
We've been understaffed all week. We've been understaffed all week.

37:00.095 --> 37:04.433
And your dad said he was too busyto come pick me up. [sighs]

37:05.100 --> 37:08.687
But look at you.You've gotten so handsome.

37:09.521 --> 37:11.231
Oh, how unfair life is.

37:12.191 --> 37:14.359
You're not supposedto get better-looking, Solomon,

37:14.443 --> 37:16.361
while I just get more wrinkles.

37:16.445 --> 37:18.197
[Solomon]What are you saying, Etsuko?

37:18.280 --> 37:19.781
You've hardly aged.

37:19.865 --> 37:21.700
[squeals] See? This is it.

37:21.783 --> 37:24.203
Why, those American girls must love you.

37:24.286 --> 37:26.288
I know. [giggles]

37:26.371 --> 37:27.789
Hey! Pajeon!

37:28.916 --> 37:29.917
[Sunja grunts]

37:32.544 --> 37:34.713
Are you crazy? Don't throw out good food!

37:34.796 --> 37:36.006
Put it down here.

37:42.304 --> 37:46.141
[Solomon sighs, clears throat]

38:03.825 --> 38:04.826
[sighs]

38:29.101 --> 38:30.310
[chuckles]

38:35.858 --> 38:37.276
"I am Rikidozan!"

38:42.406 --> 38:43.407
[sighs]

38:58.338 --> 38:59.339
[sniffs]

39:03.177 --> 39:06.555
[Etsuko] Those were Hana's favorites,weren't they?

39:08.015 --> 39:09.808
-[Solomon] Yeah.-[chuckles]

39:09.892 --> 39:11.101
[chuckles]

39:14.062 --> 39:16.064
Why do you still have them?

39:16.899 --> 39:19.401
Sentimental reasons, I suppose.

39:19.484 --> 39:20.485
[Etsuko chuckles]

39:26.450 --> 39:28.744
Has Hana contacted you?

39:30.913 --> 39:32.039
Nope. [sighs]

39:34.917 --> 39:38.921
But we hired a new detectivewho we've heard good things about.

39:39.671 --> 39:41.048
It seems hopeful.

39:53.727 --> 39:55.354
Her hand…

39:56.980 --> 39:59.399
Is it now bigger than mine?

40:00.734 --> 40:04.571
Or are they the same size? [chuckles]

40:05.155 --> 40:08.617
How can you be so certainthat she's still alive?

40:11.954 --> 40:14.581
When you have children, you'll understand.

40:17.501 --> 40:19.920
If something happens to her…

40:22.422 --> 40:24.842
… I would feel something.

40:27.344 --> 40:31.974
You would too,because you loved her, didn't you?

40:33.684 --> 40:35.936
[laughs]

40:36.019 --> 40:40.774
Your father can't stop smilingsince you've come back.

40:40.858 --> 40:45.279
I thought I was the only one who couldmake him smile like that! [chuckles]

40:46.238 --> 40:48.866
And your mother…

40:49.408 --> 40:50.909
… she would be proud.

40:52.828 --> 40:53.829
I know it.

41:04.590 --> 41:06.216
[piano chair drags on floor]

41:09.344 --> 41:13.182
["Enoya Yanoya" playing slowly on piano]

41:24.484 --> 41:27.321
Papa, something's happening outside.

41:28.864 --> 41:29.865
Sunja!

41:53.180 --> 41:54.181
[gasps]

41:55.349 --> 41:56.350
[gasps]

41:57.476 --> 41:59.311
[officer] Hurry up. Walk!

42:06.193 --> 42:07.528
[grunts]

42:08.070 --> 42:10.489
-[breathes shakily]-[officer] Get over here.

42:14.284 --> 42:15.911
[breathes shakily]

42:22.167 --> 42:24.503
[sniffles, swallows]

42:27.089 --> 42:30.843
-♪ Enoya yanoya! ♪-What are you doing?

42:32.052 --> 42:37.099
[Mr. Song] ♪ Eyano yano uhgi-ee uhcha! ♪

42:37.182 --> 42:40.060
♪ Let us go to sea ♪

42:40.143 --> 42:41.144
-Quiet!-[grunts]

42:41.228 --> 42:43.272
-[crowd gasping]-[sobs]

42:44.189 --> 42:48.235
♪ Float atop ♪

42:48.318 --> 42:52.531
-♪ The boundless expanse ♪-Enough!

42:52.614 --> 42:53.949
[grunts, gasps]

42:54.032 --> 42:55.242
[officer] You bastard!

42:55.868 --> 42:57.119
[blows landing]

42:57.202 --> 43:00.330
♪ Befriend the lone seagull ♪ ♪ Befriend the lone seagull ♪

43:00.414 --> 43:02.416
♪ We shall fight ahead ♪

43:02.499 --> 43:03.542
[grunts]

43:03.625 --> 43:04.626
[gasps]

43:05.294 --> 43:08.046
♪ Befriend the lone seagullWe shall fight ahead ♪

43:08.130 --> 43:10.591
-[Mr. Song grunts]-[gasps, sobbing]

43:10.674 --> 43:14.678
[Mr. Song] ♪ Enoya yanoya! ♪

43:14.761 --> 43:19.600
♪ Eyano yano uhgi-ee uhcha! ♪

43:19.683 --> 43:23.896
♪ Let us go to sea ♪

43:24.605 --> 43:28.108
[singing fades]

43:28.609 --> 43:30.611
[sobbing fades]

43:45.834 --> 43:46.835
[sighs]

43:50.047 --> 43:51.089
[sighs]

43:56.345 --> 43:58.180
[thunder rumbles]

44:11.818 --> 44:15.030
[siren wailing in distance]

44:38.220 --> 44:39.429
[elevator dings]

44:44.643 --> 44:45.853
Good morning.

44:52.442 --> 44:55.153
Thank you for coming, Mr. Yoshii.

45:00.075 --> 45:02.369
I saw him on television.

45:02.452 --> 45:05.289
Yes, he is a distinguished clientof the office.

45:08.208 --> 45:11.795
Welcome, Mr. Baek.I'll escort you to your office.

45:11.879 --> 45:15.924
[office worker 1]… first, which we can handle locally.

45:16.675 --> 45:18.093
Therefore, during the summer--

45:21.680 --> 45:24.516
-Please, come this way.-[officer worker continues in Japanese]

45:49.833 --> 45:51.460
[exhales softly, chuckles]

45:53.420 --> 45:56.048
-[in English] Solomon Baek.-Mr. Andrews.

45:56.924 --> 45:59.259
-Tom.-I've heard a lot about you.

45:59.343 --> 46:01.094
[clicks tongue] Be straight with me. [clicks tongue] Be straight with me.

46:02.012 --> 46:04.640
I gotta watch my back with you?Is that what this is?

46:05.349 --> 46:07.768
You don't have to worry about me.I'm not here to stay.

46:09.186 --> 46:11.688
All right. Welcome.

46:14.024 --> 46:16.443
[officer worker 2] Excuse me!Can I have your attention?

46:16.527 --> 46:17.736
[Tom clears throat]

46:18.445 --> 46:21.323
[office workers murmuring]

46:24.201 --> 46:25.410
[Tom] What's going on?

46:29.998 --> 46:32.709
[announcer on radio, in English]Japan's Emperor, Hirohito, has died.

46:32.793 --> 46:35.712
According to the official announcement,the Emperor died of cancer.

46:35.796 --> 46:37.089
He was 87 years old…

46:37.172 --> 46:39.550
[announcer 2 speaking in Spanish]

46:39.633 --> 46:42.469
[announcer 3 speaking in German]

46:46.473 --> 46:51.103
[announcer 4]Today, a nation mourns a great man…

46:51.186 --> 46:53.355
[announcer 1] He ruled duringthe Japanese occupation of Korea.

46:53.438 --> 46:55.023
[announcer 4] Once considered a god…

46:55.107 --> 46:58.151
[announcer 5] He ruled duringthe Japanese occupation of Korea…

46:58.235 --> 46:59.862
[Sunja's father retching, wheezing]

46:59.945 --> 47:03.156
… during which many familieswere separated and loved ones lost. … during which many familieswere separated and loved ones lost.

47:03.240 --> 47:06.451
[coughs, retching]

47:07.995 --> 47:08.996
[gasping]

47:10.789 --> 47:12.624
[retches, coughing]

47:14.877 --> 47:16.712
[gasping]

47:29.850 --> 47:31.685
Sunja…

47:37.191 --> 47:38.400
[wheezes]

47:41.320 --> 47:44.114
[father breathing shakily]

47:58.879 --> 47:59.880
[clears throat]

48:01.215 --> 48:02.257
Papa?

48:07.012 --> 48:08.013
Papa?

48:10.015 --> 48:11.225
[sniffles]

48:13.477 --> 48:15.103
Papa. [sobs]

48:17.314 --> 48:19.149
[cries]

48:28.033 --> 48:29.618
[Sunja's father] There was a time…

48:31.078 --> 48:33.580
… a time when I wondered…

48:34.748 --> 48:38.752
… why good fortunehad decided to pass me by.

48:39.670 --> 48:43.674
Why the everyday happinessenjoyed by others…

48:44.508 --> 48:48.345
… seemed so out of reach for me.

48:49.471 --> 48:51.682
But then your mother came along.

48:52.724 --> 48:54.351
And then you.

48:55.018 --> 48:58.647
And I realized fortunehad nothing to do with it.

48:59.731 --> 49:05.153
I had to prove myselfworthy of you, Sunja. I had to prove myselfworthy of you, Sunja.

49:07.072 --> 49:09.908
And I had to grow strong.

49:10.701 --> 49:14.538
To chase away the shadows of this world.

49:17.708 --> 49:20.544
Soon you will be strong enough yourself.

49:22.045 --> 49:25.257
And you will have your own children.

49:27.050 --> 49:31.805
And then you too will haveto prove yourself worthy.

49:34.308 --> 49:36.518
But Sunja, I know you can do it.

49:39.396 --> 49:41.231
I believe in you.

50:20.103 --> 50:22.105
[people in market chattering]

50:35.160 --> 50:36.328
Sir.

50:37.037 --> 50:39.665
It is customaryfor new fish brokers in the district

50:39.748 --> 50:41.166
to pay their respects.

50:42.835 --> 50:46.463
Yes, he is a fool,but he is still one of them.

50:50.133 --> 50:52.302
Of course I'll pay my respects.

50:52.386 --> 50:53.887
Every week in an envelope.

50:57.349 --> 51:01.061
But if he prefers something else-- But if he prefers something else--

51:01.144 --> 51:03.897
No, he wouldn't prefer that.

51:03.981 --> 51:07.484
Since you are new to our ways hereand not used to our customs--

51:07.568 --> 51:09.778
You don't need to tell me how it goes.

51:19.788 --> 51:23.208
[speaking indistinctly]

51:30.257 --> 51:31.884
[whistle blows]

51:55.616 --> 51:57.326
That girl over there, who is she?

51:58.368 --> 51:59.786
[official] Which one?

52:02.831 --> 52:04.041
That girl there.

52:04.583 --> 52:06.210
[vendor] Sunja, Sunja!

52:06.293 --> 52:08.879
I saved you the biggest one, all for you!

52:09.755 --> 52:10.756
[chuckles]

52:12.257 --> 52:13.342
[official] She's no one.

52:13.425 --> 52:16.053
[vendor]Here, look at this beauty! [laughs]

52:16.845 --> 52:21.183
Yes, I believe that her mother runssome sort of a boarding house.

52:21.266 --> 52:22.476
In Yeongdo, I think.

52:23.101 --> 52:24.311
A widow.

54:22.513 --> 54:24.765
Subtitles: DUBBING BROTHERS
